Yes. In the repo there is a file &#x27;git-icdiff&#x27; which runs the following command:<p><pre><code>    git difftool --no-prompt --extcmd icdiff &quot;$@&quot;
</code></pre>
So you can use &#x27;git icdiff&#x27; to get the icdiff display.<p>In general, you can use git-difftool in conjunction with your diff displayer of choice.
